  "text": "The HotSpot JIT compilation pipeline is built around several key architectural components:\n\n1. **CompileBroker** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compileBroker.hpp): The central broker class that manages all compilation requests. It maintains compile queues for C1 and C2, tracks compilation statistics, and coordinates the initialization and management of compiler threads.\n\n2. **CompilerThread** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compilerThread.hpp): A JavaThread subclass that executes compilation tasks. Each compiler thread is dedicated to running compilation jobs retrieved from the compile queue, and maintains its own compilation environment, logging, and task tracking.\n\n3. **Compiler (C1)** (src/hotspot/share/c1/c1_Compiler.hpp): The first-tier JIT compiler class that inherits from AbstractCompiler. It provides quick, lightweight compilation with the name \"C1\" and implements methods for initialization and compilation.\n\n4. **C2Compiler** (src/hotspot/share/opto/c2compiler.hpp): The optimizing JIT compiler class that inherits from AbstractCompiler. It provides aggressive optimizations with the name \"C2\" and implements advanced compilation strategies including escape analysis and superword optimizations.\n\n5. **AbstractCompiler** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/abstractCompiler.hpp): The base class for all JIT compilers (C1, C2, and JVMCI). It defines the common interface for compiler initialization, compilation entry points, intrinsic support, and thread management. Both C1 and C2 compilers inherit from this abstract base class to provide tiered compilation.\n\nTogether, these components form the two-tier adaptive JIT compilation system where the CompileBroker dispatches compilation work to CompilerThreads, which execute either C1 (fast) or C2 (optimized) compilation based on method hotness and compilation policies."
}

